{
  "doc_id": "44902",
  "text": "Traveling waves in reaction-diffusion systems have been investigated for a long time, and applications to biological contexts are abundant in the literature (cf. [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , and references therein). However, our principal motivating biological system, the cytoskeleton of motile cells, is not adequately described by pure reactiondiffusion equations since the advective effects of actin flow play a crucial role. A comprehensive reaction-diffusion-advection model for the actin cytoskeleton of a motile cell was established in [CITATION_3] and analyzed in [CITATION_4] . In the present paper, we investigate a simpler, prototypical reduced system that isolates features which seem essential for hyperbolic-parabolic systems with reaction such as the cell motion model of [CITATION_5] , notably regarding the formation, propagation, and interaction of waves.",
